Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.67,0:00:14.99,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I've felt since I first met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.44,0:00:18.59,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,You give me a really nostalgic feeling, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.66,0:00:26.25,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, that was a weird thing to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.70,0:00:27.69,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.31,0:00:33.45,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Narugino!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.61,0:00:36.89,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Narugino! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.66,0:00:43.64,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,These?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:47.81,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Narugino. I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.00,0:01:09.24,Punchline-Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Punch Line
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:30.00,Punchline-Ep_Title,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Brazilian High Kick
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.63,0:02:33.82,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.86,0:02:38.54,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you know \Nwhere my medication was?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.32,0:02:42.86,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Narugino,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.25,0:02:47.64,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,could you please stop becoming Strange Juice?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.61,0:02:49.44,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.44,0:02:50.86,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.86,0:02:53.69,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Your body...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.45,0:02:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.70,0:02:58.14,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,So you knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.51,0:03:00.20,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:01.45,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.88,0:03:04.95,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,There are people waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:08.14,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,But if you die, what's the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.76,0:03:10.96,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Even Ishigata-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.91,0:03:16.67,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think even Ishigata-san \Nwould have wanted that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.14,0:03:18.90,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Wait... Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.23,0:03:21.88,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about Ishigata-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.87,0:03:28.64,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Unbeijini nyopurasara,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.48,0:03:34.73,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to put a spell on you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.02,0:03:38.90,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,That song... How...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.09,0:03:41.29,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.21,0:03:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.90,0:03:47.50,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,And this body is yours,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.52,0:03:49.43,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Chiyoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.93,0:03:54.82,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.64,0:03:57.67,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you keep it from me all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:04:00.50,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I missed you, Pine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.00,0:04:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pine!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.45,0:04:08.54,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.22,0:04:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Ishigata-san saved you \Nafter you fell into that dam.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.99,0:04:16.90,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I looked for you and Guri-chan, too, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.32,0:04:19.02,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess in that rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.60,0:04:23.07,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,It was the next day that\NI realized I'd switched bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.52,0:04:26.23,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea what was going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.23,0:04:29.28,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I was so sad, I couldn't stop crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.81,0:04:34.86,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I think I would have gone crazy \Nif it weren't for Ishigata-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.85,0:04:38.71,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you came to an \Napartment in Tokyo with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:41.42,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,You know that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:46.23,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,We lived in that apartment for about a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.59,0:04:48.98,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,But one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.46,0:04:57.53,Punchline-Flashback,Ishigata,0000,0000,0000,,They're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.97,0:05:01.23,Punchline-Flashback,Ishigata,0000,0000,0000,,It's the people from the lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.60,0:05:03.38,Punchline-Flashback,Ishigata,0000,0000,0000,,Escape from the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.79,0:05:04.74,Punchline-Flashback,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.17,0:05:09.05,Punchline-Flashback,Ishigata,0000,0000,0000,,In my condition, I'll only slow you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.05,0:05:10.47,Punchline-Flashback,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.47,0:05:12.27,Punchline-Flashback,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I need you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:15.25,Punchline-Flashback,Ishigata,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.68,0:05:19.25,Punchline-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as I take care of them, \NI'll come right after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.94,0:05:22.00,Punchline-Flashback,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,You promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.22,0:05:24.34,Punchline-Flashback,Ishigata,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.38,0:05:30.47,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,But that promise was never fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.61,0:05:52.70,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Ishigata-san liked cinnamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.34,0:05:56.24,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Like, cinnamon toast and apple pie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.29,0:05:59.71,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,He loved this cinnamon tea, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.66,0:06:06.94,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was candy at first, so I bit into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.38,0:06:09.93,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Ishigata-san laughed so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.11,0:06:14.96,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Every time I smell this scent, \NI remember those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.39,0:06:18.08,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I remember the apartment, \Nand Ishigata-san's smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.83,0:06:20.19,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Chiyoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.81,0:06:23.03,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Can you try to think about it one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.38,0:06:24.94,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What did Ishigata-san want?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.37,0:06:29.15,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Why did he sacrifice himself to save you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.66,0:06:34.82,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Pine, by the way, \Ndo you remember that ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.82,0:06:37.53,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,I got in a fight over it with Guri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.53,0:06:39.34,Default,Mikatan,0000,0000,0000,,That takes me back...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.95,0:06:45.06,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Meika!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.41,0:06:46.71,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Are you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.24,0:06:48.59,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.45,0:06:52.42,Punchline-Top,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now it's time for the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.42,0:06:55.74,Punchline-Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Cold air will be blowing in \Nfrom the Sea of Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.29,0:06:56.34,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd Meika go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.74,0:06:58.22,Punchline-Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}making this evening quite chilly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.93,0:07:02.61,Punchline-Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please dress warmly if you go outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.25,0:07:03.52,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.11,0:07:05.00,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,See what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:07.38,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's not why you called?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.38,0:07:09.24,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.48,0:07:13.74,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I sent a picture to your phone \Nthis morning before I went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.74,0:07:17.50,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,It's a day late, but call it a Christmas present.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.48,0:07:19.40,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.71,0:07:20.98,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.98,0:07:22.51,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,So what did you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.04,0:07:25.00,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.31,0:07:26.30,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.30,0:07:27.96,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Quit messing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.96,0:07:30.59,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, you're no fun at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.59,0:07:33.03,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I have something important \Nto talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.03,0:07:35.26,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,It's about Narugino's condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.00,0:07:37.89,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I'm at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.89,0:07:40.25,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I had some mechanical problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.25,0:07:42.93,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on my way to buy replacement parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.57,0:07:46.00,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Can you come to my room\Nwhen you get back, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.53,0:07:47.59,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.79,0:07:49.83,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.35,0:07:56.27,Punchline-Meika_Text,Text,0000,0000,0000,,May this Christmas\Nflip your skirt up~
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.79,0:07:58.76,Punchline-Meika_Text,Text,0000,0000,0000,,May this Christmas\Nflip your skirt up~
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.17,0:08:03.93,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,That idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.93,0:08:05.31,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.22,0:08:09.84,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,A,0000,0000,0000,,Operation Intercept is \Nfundamentally doomed to fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.84,0:08:15.72,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,A,0000,0000,0000,,Nuclear weapons are powerless in space, \Nas they don't produce blast waves there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.72,0:08:18.88,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,B,0000,0000,0000,,But with a few dozen missiles...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.72,0:08:22.59,Punchline-Debate2,,0000,0000,0000,,Heated Debate!!           {\b1\fs18}TV Debate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.72,0:08:26.59,Punchline-US_Plan,,0000,0000,0000,,The US Military's Asteroid Interception Plan \NProceeding in Secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.88,0:08:22.60,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's nowhere near enough to destroy \Nan asteroid two kilometers in diameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.80,0:08:26.61,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,A,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, with a few {\i0}thousand{\i1}, \Nit might be a different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.86,0:08:31.38,Punchline-Flashback,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,The United States has secretly\Nlaunched a military satellite into orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.38,0:08:33.86,Punchline-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,equipped with several dozen nuclear missiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.50,0:08:38.01,Punchline-Flashback,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,The goal of Operation Intercept \Nis to use these missiles
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.01,0:08:39.91,Punchline-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,to destroy the incoming asteroid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.06,0:08:44.85,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Was everything he said a lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.05,0:08:49.44,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Rabura!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.90,0:08:51.37,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,You're not here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:08:57.62,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.62,0:08:59.18,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,At least knock, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.55,0:09:00.43,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Rabura?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.87,0:09:02.84,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,She left early this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.84,0:09:05.44,Default,Ito,0000,0000,0000,,She said she had an urgent \Nrequest for an exorcism.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.40,0:09:10.39,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,A,0000,0000,0000,,The number you have dialed—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.39,0:09:11.44,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.36,0:09:29.84,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What'd you do that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.15,0:09:33.09,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd make a proper \Nghostly appearance for once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.12,0:09:36.09,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,So, any leads?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.84,0:09:41.07,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I spent all day going around \Nuniversities and research labs,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.07,0:09:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,talking to physicists and space \Nengineering specialists and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.74,0:09:46.10,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,And they all said...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.10,0:09:47.44,Punchline-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.44,0:09:49.27,Punchline-Flashback,B,0000,0000,0000,,That's nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.79,0:09:52.69,Punchline-Flashback,C,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you can stop \Nit with nuclear weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.15,0:09:55.99,Punchline-Flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,But don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.50,0:10:01.37,Punchline-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,The chances of that asteroid \Nhitting Earth are slim to none.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.22,0:10:05.41,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Gliese was lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.71,0:10:11.29,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,She must've been crazy to believe \Neverything that sketchy guy said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.29,0:10:15.07,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Then that thing about him being from the U.S. \NDepartment of Defense's intelligence bureau?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.07,0:10:17.05,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,He probably made it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.91,0:10:20.18,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, tomorrow's the big day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:24.68,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Gliese visits, Miya Ken attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.37,0:10:26.88,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I finally understand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.88,0:10:30.16,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,why Miya Ken attacked Gliese.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.16,0:10:31.35,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.35,0:10:32.77,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.26,0:10:37.07,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot, I have to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.56,0:10:39.12,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,We'll continue tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.70,0:10:40.41,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.29,0:10:44.22,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.72,0:10:53.04,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you dressed like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.34,0:10:55.83,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a little under the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.83,0:10:58.79,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,I feel so hot, it's like I'm suffocating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.24,0:11:03.05,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,My cooling unit's been acting \Nweird since that guy hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:05.59,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break, would you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.59,0:11:08.23,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,What's the problem? We're both girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.23,0:11:09.76,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.76,0:11:10.59,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.59,0:11:12.06,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.06,0:11:14.59,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind, just put this on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.59,0:11:16.32,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.86,0:11:19.45,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, it's on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.17,0:11:24.91,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,That's even hotter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.23,0:11:28.55,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Is this better?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.96,0:11:33.33,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.33,0:11:34.72,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,What do I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.72,0:11:36.32,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who called me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.32,0:11:38.71,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to talk about Narugino.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.47,0:11:42.57,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,She collapsed last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.33,0:11:45.47,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,On the rooftop, after the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.25,0:11:47.86,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,It was one of those attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.86,0:11:49.98,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like she's having \Nthem more often lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.48,0:11:54.06,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I think she might be getting a lot worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.79,0:11:56.77,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,You heard from Narugino, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.77,0:11:58.23,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Meika,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.54,0:12:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can you give her a physical \Ncheckup as soon as possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.45,0:12:04.24,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know how she's doing right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:06.99,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.86,0:12:19.18,Default,Meika,0000,0000,0000,,Shouro Meiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.18,0:12:22.38,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,December 27, 8:40.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.66,0:12:23.96,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Meiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.96,0:12:27.63,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,I just got home from Utapiro \Nwith Moena and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.63,0:12:30.01,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Meiko,0000,0000,0000,,All-night karaoke is so exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.01,0:12:31.47,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Meiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:35.77,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like she's not dead yet, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.33,0:12:40.91,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,In the other history,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:44.50,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,it was early this morning \Nthat Meiko's body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.26,0:12:50.24,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,But I broke Tomoda's limbs, so now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.58,0:13:00.05,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Did I scare you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.17,0:13:03.05,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.41,0:13:05.30,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,To continue where we left off yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:06.80,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,About Gliese.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.24,0:13:08.30,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.30,0:13:12.47,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,You're not thinking about beating \Nup Gliese or anything, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.51,0:13:14.98,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.24,0:13:18.60,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Just so you know, I won't \Nlet you get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.60,0:13:19.86,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.20,0:13:22.72,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Is your head a vacuum?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.72,0:13:25.61,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Because it'll change history, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.50,0:13:28.59,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,You have to get beaten up by Rabura,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.59,0:13:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or the history where everyone \Ngets into a fight won't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.16,0:13:34.79,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,A bond without pain isn't a bond.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.79,0:13:39.39,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,The more you make amends, \Nthe stronger your ties become.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.60,0:13:44.20,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying it's important\N that they make up after fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.20,0:13:45.17,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,I told you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.54,0:13:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the cooperation of the tenants is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,vital to the success of the \NHuman Preservation Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.85,0:13:53.56,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me to just let Gliese go, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.56,0:13:55.19,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.19,0:13:59.88,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,The critical moment comes \Ntomorrow morning at 4 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.88,0:14:02.07,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,That's the moment of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.96,0:14:05.61,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,So you need to do as I say until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.61,0:14:08.34,Punchline-Gliese_Appears,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Gliese visits \NMiya Ken attacks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.38,0:14:07.32,Default,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.01,0:14:13.91,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's what this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.33,0:14:17.63,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,You tried to use me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.06,0:14:23.09,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,You thought you could get to \NMeika by getting close to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.09,0:14:24.38,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.79,0:14:27.69,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Rabura-san, please don't misunderstand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.11,0:14:27.69,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,It's just about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.69,0:14:29.12,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that I was attracted to you—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.12,0:14:30.47,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lie to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.72,0:14:33.62,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to make me happy, my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.22,0:14:31.93,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.62,0:14:35.03,Default,Rabura,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me that crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.54,0:14:38.99,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,He certainly is full of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.42,0:14:42.66,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.98,0:14:46.08,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I have a little something to say to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.08,0:14:46.99,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,To me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.22,0:14:49.71,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Is there atmosphere in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.71,0:14:53.16,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to hear your thoughts on that matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:14:58.16,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,You're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.33,0:15:08.09,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Special attack, Clam Bomb—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.48,0:15:13.10,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, is it really okay if \NI give him a flying kick?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.78,0:15:17.06,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,In order not to change history, \NI have to kick him into the pond
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.06,0:15:19.52,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,and make everyone get into a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.94,0:15:23.69,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,But then, he'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.61,0:15:30.69,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.69,0:15:32.19,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.19,0:15:34.59,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone in front \Nof me who knows the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.59,0:15:36.85,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I can't just let him get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.73,0:15:40.16,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait. I'll catch up to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.34,0:15:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Panties!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.86,0:16:11.40,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,You got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.06,0:16:18.04,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to have broken a few ribs \Nafter slamming into this rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.29,0:16:22.89,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be your fingers next if you \Ndon't answer my questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.89,0:16:25.54,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Just what do you want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.54,0:16:28.09,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,First, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:31.73,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,I'm from the U.S. Department of Defense...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.53,0:16:35.14,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Lie again and I really will break your bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.02,0:16:37.51,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think it's a lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.51,0:16:41.43,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Because everything you said\Nto Rabura was total crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.14,0:16:44.63,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,So you were eavesdropping.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.63,0:16:46.44,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.74,0:16:47.69,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Twice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.21,0:16:49.66,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.00,0:16:51.32,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you run?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.85,0:16:56.40,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone would, if someone like you \Njust showed up out of the blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.78,0:17:00.74,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting with your pinky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.74,0:17:04.08,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,After I'm done breaking the other \Nnine fingers, your molars are next.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.33,0:17:07.75,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.75,0:17:11.30,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,It won't impede the project if I tell you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.63,0:17:15.27,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a leader of the Qmay Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.27,0:17:17.81,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in charge of everything \Nregarding the project.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.53,0:17:24.85,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,True, a few nuclear missiles won't destroy VR-1.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.38,0:17:28.36,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,It'll merely change its trajectory by a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.75,0:17:31.43,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,toward a collision course with Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.20,0:17:37.66,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,The question is how to get into \Nthe impregnable AFSPC servers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.19,0:17:40.02,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Not even the most brilliant hackers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.02,0:17:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the world attacking all at once \Nstand a chance against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.82,0:17:46.54,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we looked towards...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.22,0:17:48.29,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Meika?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.76,0:17:52.30,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Her hacking skills are beyond human.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.00,0:17:56.80,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Meika isn't going to give in to your threats.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.80,0:17:59.55,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Who said we're threatening her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.75,0:18:04.42,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,She'll infiltrate the AFSPC \Nservers by her own will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.42,0:18:08.65,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,She's not going to ignore the \Npleas of her best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.88,0:18:10.65,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you needed Rabura?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.43,0:18:15.35,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Once she opens the gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.35,0:18:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all I need to do to get into \Nthe server is to tap the wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.75,0:18:26.32,Punchline-Flashback,Chiranosuke,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The critical moment comes \Ntomorrow morning at 4 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.05,0:18:29.77,Punchline-Internal/Narrator,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,That's the moment of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.85,0:18:41.26,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,I injected you with this while \Nyou were falling down the ledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.50,0:18:46.02,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Your sense of pain is dulled \Nwhile you're Uberfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.32,0:18:49.02,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,It's no wonder you didn't notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.59,0:18:52.59,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, it's just an anesthetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.59,0:18:54.77,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,You'll wake up in half a day or so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.30,0:18:58.69,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Though, you're more likely \Nto die from the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.66,0:19:01.74,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.67,0:19:04.03,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.29,0:19:07.20,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Ubermensch is impressive indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.64,0:19:13.08,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,To have so much strength even with \Nthat powerful anesthetic in you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.43,0:19:15.05,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,But don't get cocky.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.05,0:19:19.05,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the only one with that ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.91,0:19:26.68,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,No, a Face Maker!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.11,0:19:31.19,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,I got that through Chichibu Rando.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:33.82,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,It was so useful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.78,0:19:37.44,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.72,0:19:40.65,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you don't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.65,0:19:43.90,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Would you go to sleep already?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.05,0:20:00.42,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.78,0:20:09.77,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like you've figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.35,0:20:23.53,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.53,0:20:25.24,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:26.33,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.94,0:20:29.25,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I can't say it's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.65,0:20:33.70,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,We met just six days ago, Pine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.82,0:20:39.16,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Guriko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.86,0:20:42.00,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm Guriko.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.71,0:20:45.59,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,And this body's supposed to be yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.85,0:20:48.10,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,So how do you feel? Embarrassed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.85,0:20:53.19,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,I won't force you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.72,0:20:56.36,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Human history is nearly over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.36,0:20:59.44,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,Living with your eyes averted from \Nthat reality isn't a bad option.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.84,0:21:02.44,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.89,0:21:05.52,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,People change after nine years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.03,0:21:08.95,Default,Gliese,0000,0000,0000,,You're the ones who are odd,\Nfor not having changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.19,0:21:11.45,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.56,0:21:16.33,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,The Guriko I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.00,0:21:27.35,Default,Yuta,0000,0000,0000,,Guriko...
